      "channelName": "💬-discussion",
      "summary": "The discussion channel covered several key topics. A critical issue emerged regarding the ai16z token migration, with odilitime confirming the migration period has closed, leaving nelsonlopes_ unable to migrate approximately $700-900 worth of tokens. A scam incident occurred where nelsonlopes_ lost funds through a fraudulent support ticket, with community members advising to block and report the scammers. On the technical side, cacophonousstrife sought guidance on building examples from the ElizaOS documentation, with odilitime directing them to the GitHub examples directory at github.com/elizaOS/eliza/tree/v2.0.0/examples. The community discussed ElizaOS v3 development, with satsbased announcing it's nearly ready and will enable agents to generate revenue. A significant clarification was provided about the ElizaOK product: baogerbao explained that ElizaOK is built with elizacloud, has no separate token currently, and all users registered under elizaok flow into elizacloud. Questions arose about the relationship between ElizaOS, ElizaOK, and elizacloud, with baogerbao deferring detailed business model explanations to odilitime. The token deployment was clarified as being on Solana, BSC, and Base chains. Technical support was requested for minimax token plan key integration as a provider plugin, though this remained unresolved. Community engagement initiatives were emphasized, with calls to interact with Shaw's posts and share development updates.",
