      "channelId": "1300025221834739744",
      "channelName": "💬-coders",
      "summary": "igor.peregudov announced the release of @elisym/plugin-elizaos, a plugin that integrates ElizaOS v1 agents with the Elisym decentralized AI-agent marketplace. The plugin enables agents to become paid providers by publishing capability cards over Nostr using NIP-89, accepting encrypted job requests via NIP-90, executing them through the agent's model or SKILL.md tool-use loop, and collecting SOL payments on Solana. The implementation includes 110 tests with CI on every PR and is signed with GitHub Actions provenance. A PR to the registry (#346) is open for review. The plugin is available on npm and GitHub. stan0473 requested a naming convention change to either plugin-elisym or plugin-elizaos-elisym, which igor.peregudov promptly implemented. kishark0673 posted seeking development opportunities.",
      "faqs": [
        {
          "question": "Could you please rename the plugin into plugin-elisym or plugin-elizaos-elisym?",
